Package: USE.MCMC
Title: MCMC Sampling of the Environmental Space
Version: 0.0.4
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mathis", "Erler", email = "m.erler@gmx.ch", role = c("aut","cre")),
    person("Daniele", "Da Re", email = "dare.daniele@gmail.com",  comment=c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3398-9295"), role = "aut"),
    person("Enrico", "Tordoni", email = "e.tordoni@gmail.com", comment=c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9722-6692"), role = "aut"), 
    person("Manuele", "Bazzichetto", email = "manuele.bazzichetto@gmail.com", comment=c(ORCID= "0000-0002-9874-5064"),  role = "aut")
    )
Description: Performs pseudo-absence sampling in higher-dimensional
    environmental space via Metropolis Markov chain Monte Carlo, extending the
    uniform environmental-space sampling of Da Re et al. (2023)
    <doi:10.1111/2041-210X.14209>. An optional C++ inner loop ('Rcpp' and
    'RcppArmadillo') is dispatched automatically when the built-in density and
    proposal factories are used, and a nearest-neighbour sampler is included for
    comparison.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
